      • getSQLLexicalFormDatetime

        public String getSQLLexicalFormDatetime(String v)
        Given an XSD dateTime this method will generate a SQL TIMESTAMP value. The method will strip any fractional seconds found in the date time (since we haven't found a nice way to support them in all databases). It will also normalize the use of Z to the timezome +00:00 and last, if the database is H2, it will remove all timezone information, since this is not supported there.
        Specified by:
        getSQLLexicalFormDatetime in interface SQLDialectAdapter
        Overrides:
        getSQLLexicalFormDatetime in class SQL99DialectAdapter
        Returns:
